When should I see a doctor for Ankle Injury ?
The sooner you see a foot specialist, the better the diagnosis and treatment will be! Any severe ankle injury need to be evaluated by an orthopedic surgeon; this includes:
- Anxiety or pain;
- History of trauma;
- Numbness of the foot or leg, which can be caused by injuries to the neurovascular bundle (nerves and blood vessels that run across the front of the ankle);
- Poorly healing injury in the ankles;
- Redness, swelling, warmth or tenderness;
- Stiffness of the joint;
- Swelling;
- Traumatic injury;
- Tenderness to palpation.
